import Title from '../title/title.js'; import './schedule.css'; const Schedule = () => (
<div className='schedule-items'> <h1 style={{ fontWeight: 'normal' }}><img src='https://icon.now.sh/event/A7BBCE/50' alt='' />Mark your calendars, the Rice Datathon will take place January 24-25, 2020</h1> <h1 style={{ fontWeight: 'normal' }}><img src='https://icon.now.sh/pin/A7BBCE/50' alt='' />The Datathon will be held in <a href="https://goo.gl/maps/m3tKWrdj84y5RpY6A" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Duncan Hall</a> on the Rice Campus</h1> <h1 style={{ fontWeight: 'normal' }}>Order of Events</h1> <h2 style={{ fontWeight: 'normal' }}>Friday Jan 24th</h2> <ul> <li></li> </ul> </div> </div> ) export default Schedule;
